;(Talk to Senior at Leisure)
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' Oh? It's rare to see someone walking down this street.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's rare to see someone walking down this street.
::'''Senior at Leisure:''' Oho, then you must be a regular to this commercial street, too.
::'''Senior at Leisure:''' I take my strolls around here, but I've never seen you before.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Aren't you scared?
::'''Senior at Leisure:''' Haha, it's just a small commercial street. What's there to be scared about?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's dangerous to be in the Fragmentum!
::'''Senior at Leisure:''' Fragmentum? I don't know what you're talking about, but I'll be careful. Thank you, kid.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What a stubborn old man.
::'''Senior at Leisure:''' Haha, I'll head back early if you insist.
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' I may look old and useless now, but I once fought on the battlefield with Madam Alisa... Nothing will faze me.
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' Besides, I'm old now. I don't get surprised anymore.
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' Hmm, I do have a gadget with me from before the war. It can help us talk to people across the skies and memorialize your surroundings in images. Pity it's broken now, and no one knows how to fix it anymore...
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' Kiddo, what you have in your hand looks similar to my gadget &mdash; Can I please ask you to give a good look at this thing?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Of course.
:'''Senior at Leisure:''' Thank you, kid. I hope this won't take a lot of your time.
